---
import "../styles/global.css";
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="favicon.png" />
<title>TermCoder — dashboard</title>
<meta name="description" content="Your TermCoder dashboard — models, synced sessions, recipes, MCP connectors, and study decks in one place." />
</head>
<body class="sys dash">

<header class="sys-nav">
  <div class="in-row">
    <div class="mark-cell"><span class="brand-mark" aria-hidden="true"></span></div>
    <div class="row">
      <a class="wordmark" href="index.html">TERMCODER</a>
      <nav class="links">
        <a href="index.html">Home</a>
        <a href="features.html">Features</a>
        <a href="docs.html">Docs</a>
      </nav>
      <div class="acct">
        <img class="acct-avatar" alt="" />
        <span class="acct-name">you@example.com</span>
        <a class="acct-out" href="login.html" data-signout>Sign out</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="dash-wrap">
  <aside class="dash-side">
    <button class="dash-tab on" data-tab="overview">Overview</button>
    <button class="dash-tab" data-tab="models">Models</button>
    <button class="dash-tab" data-tab="sessions">Sessions</button>
    <button class="dash-tab" data-tab="recipes">Recipes</button>
    <button class="dash-tab" data-tab="connectors">Connectors</button>
    <button class="dash-tab" data-tab="study">Study</button>
    <button class="dash-tab" data-tab="settings">Settings</button>
  </aside>

  <section class="dash-main">

    <div class="dash-panel on" data-panel="overview">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> OVERVIEW</div>
      <h2>Welcome back<span data-greet></span>.</h2>
      <p class="dash-sub">Everything you sync from the app and CLI, in one place. Nothing here is billed —
        TermCoder runs with no API key and no account; this only mirrors your own data.</p>
      <div class="stat-grid">
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-k">Default model</span><span class="stat-v">termcoder/auto</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-k">Study streak</span><span class="stat-v" data-stat="streak">—</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-k">Due today</span><span class="stat-v" data-stat="study-due">—</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-k">Decks</span><span class="stat-v" data-stat="study-decks">—</span></div>
      </div>
      <h3 class="dash-h3">Your decks</h3>
      <div class="dash-list" data-deck-list>
        <div class="dash-empty">Sign in and sync from the app to see your study decks here.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dash-panel" data-panel="models">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> MODELS</div>
      <h2>Pick your engine.</h2>
      <p class="dash-sub">Start on the keyless model with no setup, then connect a stronger one whenever you
        want. TermCoder never downgrades your choice.</p>
      <div class="dash-list">
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">termcoder/auto</span><span class="dash-c2">routes to your best available</span><span class="badge-2 ok">ready</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">termexplorer/auto</span><span class="dash-c2">study &amp; schoolwork tutor</span><span class="badge-2 ok">ready</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">termcoderfree/auto</span><span class="dash-c2">keyless — no API key needed</span><span class="badge-2 ok">ready</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">anthropic/claude-sonnet-5</span><span class="dash-c2">complex tasks</span><span class="badge-2">needs key</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">google/gemini-2.5-pro</span><span class="dash-c2">free tier available</span><span class="badge-2">needs key</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">ollama/llama3.1</span><span class="dash-c2">local · unlimited · private</span><span class="badge-2 local">local</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dash-panel" data-panel="sessions">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> SESSIONS <span class="dash-sample">sample</span></div>
      <h2>Your work, synced.</h2>
      <p class="dash-sub">Session sync is on the way — once it lands, the sessions you sync via GitHub will
        show up here so you can resume on any machine. Below is a sample of how it looks.</p>
      <div class="dash-list">
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Refactor auth middleware</span><span class="dash-c2">termcoder/auto · 42 turns</span><a class="dash-open" href="download.html">Open</a></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Payment webhook debugging</span><span class="dash-c2">anthropic/claude-sonnet-5 · 18 turns</span><a class="dash-open" href="download.html">Open</a></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Krebs cycle — review</span><span class="dash-c2">termexplorer/auto · 9 cards</span><a class="dash-open" href="download.html">Open</a></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Migrate build to esbuild</span><span class="dash-c2">termcoder/auto · 27 turns</span><a class="dash-open" href="download.html">Open</a></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dash-panel" data-panel="recipes">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> RECIPES <span class="dash-sample">sample</span></div>
      <h2>Saved workflows.</h2>
      <p class="dash-sub">Named, shareable multi-step tasks — dev automations that run in order, or study
        lessons taught one step at a time. You create and run these in the app today; syncing them here is
        on the way. Below is a sample.</p>
      <div class="dash-list">
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">open-pr</span><span class="dash-c2">branch, push, open a PR</span><span class="badge-2 tag">dev · 3 steps</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">test-and-fix</span><span class="dash-c2">run tests, fix failures, re-run</span><span class="badge-2 tag">dev · 3 steps</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">release</span><span class="dash-c2">bump, tag, publish</span><span class="badge-2 tag">dev · 3 steps</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">photosynthesis</span><span class="dash-c2">guided lesson, one step at a time</span><span class="badge-2 tag">study · 5 steps</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dash-panel" data-panel="connectors">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> CONNECTORS</div>
      <h2>One-click MCP.</h2>
      <p class="dash-sub">Add a Model Context Protocol server without memorizing commands. Pick a connector,
        fill in what it needs, and its tools appear to the agent.</p>
      <div class="dash-list">
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">GitHub</span><span class="dash-c2">issues, PRs, code · hosted</span><a class="dash-open" href="docs.html">Add</a></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Filesystem</span><span class="dash-c2">read &amp; write a chosen folder</span><a class="dash-open" href="docs.html">Add</a></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Web fetch</span><span class="dash-c2">fetch a URL as clean markdown</span><a class="dash-open" href="docs.html">Add</a></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">PostgreSQL</span><span class="dash-c2">query a database, read-only</span><a class="dash-open" href="docs.html">Add</a></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Brave Search</span><span class="dash-c2">web &amp; local search</span><a class="dash-open" href="docs.html">Add</a></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dash-panel" data-panel="study">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> STUDY</div>
      <h2>Decks &amp; streak.</h2>
      <p class="dash-sub">TermExplorer turns the same engine into a tutor — spaced-repetition flashcards that
        resurface at the right time. Your decks and streak sync here.</p>
      <div class="stat-grid">
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-k">Current streak</span><span class="stat-v" data-stat="study-streak">6 days</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-k">Due today</span><span class="stat-v" data-stat="study-due">12 cards</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-k">Decks</span><span class="stat-v" data-stat="study-decks">4</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dash-list" data-deck-list>
        <div class="dash-empty">Sign in and sync from the app to see your study decks here.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dash-panel" data-panel="settings">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> SETTINGS <span class="dash-sample">sample</span></div>
      <h2>Your preferences.</h2>
      <p class="dash-sub">These travel with your account. Everything is optional — sensible defaults are
        already set. Editing them here is on the way; the values below are the defaults.</p>
      <div class="dash-list">
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Display name</span><span class="dash-c2">shown in live rooms</span><span class="set-val">you</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Theme</span><span class="dash-c2">app color theme</span><span class="set-val">ember</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Default model</span><span class="dash-c2">used for new sessions</span><span class="set-val">termcoder/auto</span></div>
        <div class="dash-row"><span class="dash-c1">Sync via GitHub</span><span class="dash-c2">mirror sessions, decks, recipes</span><span class="badge-2 ok">on</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="row-2">
        <a class="btn-2" href="docs.html">Read the docs</a>
        <a class="btn-2" href="login.html" data-signout>Sign out</a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </section>
</main>

<script is:inline>
  (function () {
    var tabs = document.querySelectorAll(".dash-tab");
    var panels = document.querySelectorAll(".dash-panel");
    function show(name) {
      tabs.forEach(function (t) { t.classList.toggle("on", t.dataset.tab === name); });
      panels.forEach(function (p) { p.classList.toggle("on", p.dataset.panel === name); });
    }
    tabs.forEach(function (t) {
      t.addEventListener("click", function () { show(t.dataset.tab); });
    });
  })();
</script>
<script is:inline src="config.js?v=3"></script>
<script is:inline src="auth.js?v=6"></script>

</body>
</html>
